% Shared defaults for the non-image bespoke frontpages: star, flower, and circle.
% These covers all follow the same four-block model:
% 1) title/subtitle, 2) author/address, 3) translator, 4) publisher/logo.
% The per-style setup macros below only override these shared defaults.
%
% Naming convention for the layout variables:
% - *xoffset: horizontal shift from the anchor line. Use a TeX length such as
%   `-0.04\paperwidth` or `12pt`.
% - *fromtop / *frombottom: vertical placement expressed as a TeX length
%   measured from the named page edge. Use values such as `0.10\paperheight`
%   or `42pt`.
% - *anchor: which edge or corner the text node is attached to. The matching
%   coordinate builder interprets this and chooses the correct page edge.
% - *align: paragraph alignment inside the node. This controls multi-line text
%   layout, not the node position itself.
% - *width / *fontsize: node text width and the base font size for that block.
%
% Editing advice:
% - Prefer changing these normalized values instead of touching the renderer
%   code below. That preserves the shared override API from `\customizefrontpage`.
% - For ornate covers, title and author blocks usually stay tied to the right
%   side, so change `fromtop`, `width`, and sizes first before changing anchors.
% - The coordinate macros below are derived values only; do not edit them by hand.
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetitlexoffset}{-0.04\paperwidth}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetitlefromtop}{0.10\paperheight}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetitleanchor}{north east}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetitlealign}{right}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetitlewidth}{0.95\paperwidth}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetitlefontsize}{33}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatesubtitlefontsize}{15}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornateauthorxoffset}{-0.04\paperwidth}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornateauthorfromtop}{0.34\paperheight}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornateauthoranchor}{north east}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornateauthoralign}{right}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornateauthorwidth}{0.95\paperwidth}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornateauthorfontsize}{22}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornateauthoraddressfontsize}{13}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetranslatorxoffset}{0pt}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetranslatorfrombottom}{0.22\paperheight}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetranslatoranchor}{south}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetranslatoralign}{center}
\newcommand{\bookish@ornatetranslatorwidth}{0.50\paperwidth}
